## HYPOTHESIS_MATRIX
- empathy_uses_runtime_direct_transport: SUPPORTED — Direct `api.runtime.subagent.run()` call at line 193, no registry pattern detected.
- empathy_has_unverified_openclaw_hook_assumptions: SUPPORTED — SDK types define hook but delivery guarantee not verified; no test confirms hook always fires.
- empathy_timeout_leads_to_false_completion: SUPPORTED — TTL cleanup (line 269-277) releases sessionLock and deletes from activeRuns without completing observer work.
- empathy_cleanup_not_idempotent: UNPROVEN — completedSessions map provides dedup, but concurrent finalizeRun and subagent_ended could both call reapBySession; race window exists.
- empathy_lacks_dedupe_key: SUPPORTED — idempotencyKey `${sessionId}:${Date.now()}` passed to run() but not stored at workflow level; rapid re-triggers could spawn duplicates within same ms.

